Definition: an interest followed with exaggerated zeal
Example: he always follows the latest fads; it was all the rage that season
Synonyms: adj, all, fashionable, faddy, noun, person, faddist, craze, enthusiastic, crazy, furor, furore, cult, rage, fashion, an, interest, followed, with, exaggerated, zeal, he, always, follows, the, latest, fads, it, was, that, season
Category: noun.cognition
